## Setup

```bash
uv sync
git init
uv run pre-commit install
```

Copy `config.toml` and update the paths for your machine:

```bash
cp config.toml config.local.toml  # optional: keep a local override
```

Edit `config.toml` to point `data_root` and `results_root` at the right locations.
The generated config uses grouped dataclasses: `PathsConfig` is one example section,
and you can add new groups such as `PreprocessingConfig` or `AnalysisConfig` with
matching TOML sections as your project grows.

## Project layout

```
src/{{ package_name }}/
    config.py         # load_config() + CONFIG singleton
    io/               # data loading
    preprocessing/    # signal preprocessing
    analysis/         # analysis functions
scripts/              # numbered analysis scripts
results/              # figures and outputs (not committed)
```

